House Resolution 402
By: Representatives Stinson of the 150th, Jackson of the 68th, and Hugley of the 141st
A RESOLUTION
1 Commending Reign Over Cancer Inc.; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Reign Over Cancer Inc. has a long and consistent record of service to the
3 community and has been recognized as one of the most dynamic and committed
4 organizations in Georgia; and
5 WHEREAS, Reign Over Cancer Inc. is a nonprofit entity founded by Reign Stevens, a breast
6 cancer survivor, who uses her experience as a lobbyist, community organizer, legislative
7 aide, and certified life coach to raise awareness and provide solutions to issues surrounding
8 post-cancer treatment life; and
9 WHEREAS, this remarkable nonprofit fosters partnerships with grassroots organizations and
10 medical professionals to bridge gaps, increase awareness, and find solutions for those in
11 need; and
12 WHEREAS, Reign Over Cancer Inc. has provided hundreds of children of survivors with
13 Christmas gifts and recognizes these children as "silent survivors" who are deeply affected
14 by their parents' ongoing battles with cancer; and
